questionRound.0.question.9.answer: Just need to find the dominant strategy of the last player (player at the right side) in every round  and work the way back. Some players however were irrational/didn't understand how to play  so I couldn't win the most tokens possible in some rounds.

If I was the last player  meaning there were no other choices to be made after me- it was fairly easy: I simply chose the option with the highest payout. On the other side  if someone were after me I chose the option that most probably would get me a 'good' payout  based off of what they most likely would have chosen on their end

strategies are different depending on the role you are playing. In the premise that every player will make rational decision  you should consider what others will choose to make your own decision. At the same time  other players' decision will also be affected by yours. |
Working backwards to guess what the next person would choose based off of your own answer if applicable.

1. I assume that everyone wants the most payoff among their choices. | 2. I infer what the person will choose based on my choice  then it is easy to infer what the person that decides my payoff will choose  then I choose the most payoff based on his choice. |

It took me 1-2 matches to get the hang of it (the first test match wasn't enough for me to see what choices I made would ensure maximum points or how my decisions affected other's choices). Once I figured it out  I always did back calculation to see what the last person (person 3  say) would choose depending on my selected answer  and then what the person before him (person 2) would choose. Many a times I would not get the max number of points even though one of my cells would display it  because of a choice I thought the other people would make. In those cases  I selected the cell which would ensure me the 'relatively' highest number of points that I could get  if those calculated choices I thought they would make  were made.
Look at the connections between each color.

The last person often had his two highest numbers in the same row  so I could conclude that he would choose that row and that (hopefully) the other people in my group would also know he would choose that row. Therefore  once I knew his choice  I could determine everyone else's choices by assuming that they would take the highest amount available to them. I based my choice off of the highest number available to me once I had guessed the choices of others. For example  on Display 7  I knew Green would choose XG because the two highest numbers are both in XG. Assuming Blue also knew he would choose XG  Blue would choose YB because the number in XG/YB is higher than that in XG/XB. By the same logic  Red would choose XR  which would make the best choice for me XO. Basically  the last person often had control over what everyone else did  even though they made their choice last. |  | If the last person's answer was not easily determined  I would look at the highest number of my four boxes. I would figure out what had to happen in order for me to get that number  based on the assumption that everyone else was also trying to get the highest number possible. If I found that someone else would probably make a choice that would give me the lower number of the two in my chosen row  I would pick the other row in order to get the highest number in that one.
I analysis from the last player to the first player. The last player's choice will affect the former's choice.

I was trying to figure out what my co-mates would choose. based on the instructions  we knew that it was an individual gain/loss game  which means that I am in it for myself. I am not depending on anyone else's fortune and can accumulate money solely to my own choices. this holdes true for all of the other players. And given that I am a realist  I think  everyone is trying to get the most money without sabotaging anyone else. Therefore I always chose what would be the most profitable to my payoffs.
Selected the highest number in each box  depending on what order i was in(blue red green or orange.) If i was last  i selected the highest number since that would be my payoff.
I would follow it like a path....follow the yellow brick road!
